annotationA: Birt-Hogg-Dube homolog; It is involved in the biological process described with: negative regulation of transcription of nuclear large rRNA transcript from RNA polymerase I promoter; germ-line stem cell maintenance; negative regulation of RNA polymerase I regulatory region sequence-specific DNA binding
annotationB: GATOR complex protein MIOS; Involved in the differentiation of the oocyte nucleus. Influences meiotic progression prior to pachytene and possibly by interacting with pathways that control DNA metabolism. May act in the oocyte nucleus to facilitate the execution of the unique cell cycle and developmental programs that produce the mature haploid gamete. Required for the regulation of the TORC1 pathway by amino acids
